Title: Sample Story
Author: AI Adaptation


INT. COFFEE SHOP - DAY

Sarah enters the dimly lit coffee shop, her heart racing. She scans the room. John sits at a corner table, his face illuminated by his laptop.

JOHN
	He stands.
	Sarah. Thank you for coming.
	Sarah sits across from him, placing her bag on the empty chair beside her.

SARAH
	What's so important that it couldn't wait?
	John closes his laptop and leans forward.

JOHN
	I found something. Something that changes everything.

SARAH
	What are you talking about?
	He reaches into his jacket pocket and pulls out a small, weathered notebook.

JOHN
	This belonged to my grandfather. It contains a map — a map to something valuable.

SARAH
	Sarah raises an eyebrow.
	A map? What kind of map?

JOHN
	(whispering)
	The kind that people would kill for.
	His eyes dart around the coffee shop nervously.

INT. JOHN'S APARTMENT - MORNING

Sarah arrives. The apartment is a disaster. Papers are scattered everywhere, books piled high on every surface.

SARAH
	What happened here?
	She steps carefully over a stack of old newspapers.

JOHN (O.S.)
	Someone broke in last night. But they didn't find what they were looking for.
	John emerges from the kitchen, holding up a notebook.

JOHN
	The map is written in code. My grandfather was paranoid, but it turns out his paranoia was justified.
	Sarah takes the notebook. She examines the strange symbols.

SARAH
	This looks like a substitution cipher. I think I can decode it.
	John watches her, hope flickering in his eyes.

JOHN
	If you can crack this, we might actually have a chance.

INT. JOHN'S APARTMENT - EVENING

Hours pass. The sun sets outside. Sarah finally looks up from the notebook.

SARAH
	I've got it. The map leads to a location in the old cemetery on the outskirts of town.

JOHN
	Together?
	Sarah nods.

SARAH
	Together.